HEADWORD: Araucariaceae
<hw>Araucariaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>a
family of tall evergreen cone-bearing trees of South America and
Australia with broad leathery leaves; in some classifications included
in the Pinaceae.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Araucariaceae</fam>, araucaria
family</syn>⟦br⟧
